    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 171 
                    The Joint Chiefs of Staff to the
                        Commanding General, United States Military Mission in the Soviet Union
                        (
                        Deane
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d171</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">171</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-27T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="171" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J. C. S.</gloss> Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 171 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to the
                        Commanding General, United States Military Mission in the Soviet Union</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_DMGJR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Deane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-27">27 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">War</hi> 23447. <gloss target="#t_topsec1">TopSec</gloss>
                    to <persName corresp="#p_DMGJR1">Deane</persName> from the Joint Chiefs of
                    Staff.</p>
                <p>With regard to U. S.–Russian military conversations at the forthcoming
                    conference, the United States Chiefs of Staff will be prepared <pb facs="0327" n="195" xml:id="pg_195"/> to exchange with the Russians estimates of the
                    Japanese situation and to discuss plans for the conduct of the war against
                        <persName corresp="#p_J1">Japan</persName>, with a view to effecting
                    necessary coordination. They will be glad to discuss other appropriate subjects
                    desired by the Russians. You should request the Soviet General Staff to advise
                    the United States Chiefs of Staff in the near future as to additional subjects
                    they may desire to discuss.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
